      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>meat-free mince</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cumin</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and the <strong>grated red onion</strong></p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>half </strong>of the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (save the rest for later!) and mix thoroughly until fully combined (clean hands is the best way!)</p><p>Cut two A3 size sheets of<strong> non-stick baking paper</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1629462017198-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1629462017198-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
